  </mstyle>
</math>
<asciimath>""_r ii(S)_n</asciimath></stem>. From relation (23) given in <eref type="inline" bibitemid="muller" citeas="[1]"/> we conclude that, for <stem type="MathML" block="false"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mstyle displaystyle="false">
    <mi>r</mi>
    <mo>≥</mo>
    <mn>2</mn>
  </mstyle>
</math>
<asciimath>r &gt;= 2</asciimath></stem> and even,</p>

<formula id="eq7"><stem type="MathML" block="true"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mstyle displaystyle="true">
